"#\" id=\"singlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportSubtopicsButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"pdfWithChildren\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportBundleButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"wholeBundlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicShare zDocsShareButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Share\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex zDocsShareDialogButton\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Share\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none zDocsShareDialogButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg>Share</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareEmail\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Email Link</span></a><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareLink\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Copy Link</span></a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsFeedback zDocsFeedback zDocsTopicFeedback\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Feedback\" class=\"zDocsFeedbackButton d-none d-lg-flex\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2533571\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-tooltip-content=\"Feedback\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2533571\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Dez 30, 2022</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104wxh1665703131924.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/wxh1665703131924.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/wxh1665703131924.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"wxh1665703131924\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"wxh1665703131924__ufgetc_402512\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Get additional data from a field displayed in a Uniface component.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section refsyn\" id=\"wxh1665703131924__topic_d119633e1_d119634e1_d119635e1\">\n<div class=\"p\">\n<div class=\"zDocsCodeExplanationContainer\"><button aria-label=\"Explain this code\" class=\"zDocsAiActionsButton\" data-target=\"#zDocsCodeExplanationModal_uniface_104wxh1665703131924_html_0\" data-toggle=\"modal\" tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-code-explanation\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-code-explanation\"></use></svg>Explain this code</button></div><div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre codeblock language-plaintext\" data-explanation-rendered=\"true\" id=\"wxh1665703131924__codeblock_ojp_xnt_zvb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">short ufgetc (unsigned char* field, unsigned char* buffer, short max );</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"wxh1665703131924__topic_d85207e1_d85208e1_d85209e1_d85210e1_d85211e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1234981e61\">Parameters</h2>\n<dl class=\"dl parml\" id=\"wxh1665703131924__parml_d3r_ynt_zvb\">\n<dt class=\"dt pt dlterm\"><var class=\"keyword varname\">field</var></dt>\n<dd class=\"dd pd\">The name of the field. To resolve ambiguity, the name can be fully qualified, for\n                  example, <kbd class=\"ph userinput\">field . entity</kbd>.</dd>\n<dt class=\"dt pt dlterm\"><var class=\"keyword varname\">buffer</var></dt>\n<dd class=\"dd pd\">(Output) The buffer that is to receive the field contents.</dd>\n<dt class=\"dt pt dlterm\"><var class=\"keyword varname\">max</var></dt>\n<dd class=\"dd pd\">The size of the buffer pointed to by <var class=\"keyword varname\">buffer</var>. Ensure that this\n                  value is not larger than the actual size of the buffer.</dd>\n</dl>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"wxh1665703131924__topic_d85212e1_d85213e1_d85214e1_d85215e1_d85216e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1234981e106\">Return Values</h2>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"wxh1665703131924__d7131e20\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 1. </span><span class=\"title\">Values returned by ufget and ufgetc</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"wxh1665703131924__d7131e20__entry__1\">Value</th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"wxh1665703131924__d7131e20__entry__2\">Description</th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"wxh1665703131924__d7131e20__entry__1\">\n&gt;0\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"wxh1665703131924__d7131e20__entry__2\">The number of\nbytes copied into the buffer</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"wxh1665703131924__d7131e20__entry__1\">Zero </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"wxh1665703131924__d7131e20__entry__2\">An error occurred</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"wxh1665703131924__d7131e20__entry__1\">&lt;0 </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"wxh1665703131924__d7131e20__entry__2\">The negated number of bytes copied into the\n                        buffer. The negative status indicates that more data is available in the\n                        field and that you should call <code class=\"ph codeph\">ufgetc</code>  to get that\n                        additional data. </td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"wxh1665703131924__topic_d85217e1_d85218e1_d85219e1_d85220e1_d85221e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1234981e170\">Use</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"wxh1665703131924__d5947e20\">Library:  <span class=\"ph filepath\">yrtl</span>\n</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"wxh1665703131924__topic_d85222e1_d85223e1_d85224e1_d85225e1_d85226e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1234981e183\">Description</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"wxh1665703131924__p_d119663e1_d119664e1_d119665e1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">ufgetc</code> moves an additional chunk\n            of data from a component field into the specified buffer. This function should be called\n            only after an initial call to <code class=\"ph codeph\">ufget</code> or <code class=\"ph codeph\">ufgetc</code> returned\n            a negative value, which indicates there is more data available.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"wxh1665703131924__p_d119666e1_d119667e1_d119668e1\">Parameters and return values are the same as for\n               <code class=\"ph codeph\">ufget</code>, so if <code class=\"ph codeph\">ufgetc</code> also returns a negative status,\n            it must be called repeatedly until a positive status is returned.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"wxh1665703131924__p_d119669e1_d119670e1_d119671e1\">See the description of <code class=\"ph codeph\">ufget</code> for\n            additional information and example code.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"wxh1665703131924__section_rlr_g4t_zvb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1234981e215\">Example: ufget and ufgetc</h2>\n<p class=\"p\">The following example illustrates how to use <code class=\"ph codeph\">ufget</code>,\n               <code class=\"ph codeph\">ufgetc</code>, and <code class=\"ph codeph\">ugetbind</code> to read data from a specified\n            (but arbitrary) field data into a buffer. Because the size of the field is unknown, the\n            example reads fixed chunks and expands the buffer as necessary. The choice of 100 as the\n            size of the fixed chunks is arbitrary.</p>\n<div class=\"zDocsCodeExplanationContainer\"><button aria-label=\"Explain this code\" class=\"zDocsAiActionsButton\" data-target=\"#zDocsCodeExplanationModal_uniface_104wxh1665703131924_html_1\" data-toggle=\"modal\" tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-code-explanation\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-code-explanation\"></use></svg>Explain this code</button></div><div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre codeblock language-plaintext\" data-explanation-rendered=\"true\" id=\"wxh1665703131924__codeblock_qwx_h4t_zvb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">#include &lt;h3gl.h&gt;\n#define CHUNKSIZE 100\nEXPORT void getfield (char* fldname)\n{\nchar bindname[80];\nchar* buf;\nint len;\nint totlen;\nugetbind(fldname, bindname); /* Get bindname for efficiency */\nbuf = malloc(CHUNKSIZE); /* Allocate the buffer */\n/* Get the first chunk of data */\nlen = ufget(bindname, buf, CHUNKSIZE);\ntotlen = abs(len); /* Set total length */\nwhile ( len &lt; 0 ) /* More to come */\n{ /* Make room for next chunk */\nbuf = realloc(buf, totlen+CHUNKSIZE);\n/* Get next chunk */\nlen = ufgetc(bindname, buf+totlen, CHUNKSIZE);\n/* Update total length */\ntotlen += abs(len);\n}\nbuf = realloc(buf, totlen+1); /* Make room for terminator */\nbuf[totlen] = 0; /* Add terminator */\n}</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/lyr1665703131793.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>ufget</a><p>Get data from a field displayed in a Uniface component.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ene1665703131995.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>ugetbind</a><p>Get the internal bind name of a Uniface field.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2533571\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2533571\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "ufgetc Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Dez 30, 2022 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Get additional data from a field displayed in a Uniface component. Explain this code short ufgetc (unsigned char* field, unsigned char* buffer, short max ); Copy Parameters field The name of the field. To resolve ambiguity, the name can be fully qualified, for example, field . entity . buffer (Output) The buffer that is to receive the field contents. max The size of the buffer pointed to by buffer . Ensure that this value is not larger than the actual size of the buffer. Return Values Table 1. Values returned by ufget and ufgetc Value Description >0 The number of bytes copied into the buffer Zero An error occurred <0 The negated number of bytes copied into the buffer. The negative status indicates that more data is available in the field and that you should call ufgetc to get that additional data. Use Library: yrtl Description ufgetc moves an additional chunk of data from a component field into the specified buffer. This function should be called only after an initial call to ufget or ufgetc returned a negative value, which indicates there is more data available. Parameters and return values are the same as for ufget , so if ufgetc also returns a negative status, it must be called repeatedly until a positive status is returned. See the description of ufget for additional information and example code. Example: ufget and ufgetc The following example illustrates how to use ufget , ufgetc , and ugetbind to read data from a specified (but arbitrary) field data into a buffer. Because the size of the field is unknown, the example reads fixed chunks and expands the buffer as necessary. The choice of 100 as the size of the fixed chunks is arbitrary. Explain this code #include <h3gl.h> #define CHUNKSIZE 100 EXPORT void getfield (char* fldname) { char bindname[80]; char* buf; int len; int totlen; ugetbind(fldname, bindname); /* Get bindname for efficiency */ buf = malloc(CHUNKSIZE); /* Allocate the buffer */ /* Get the first chunk of data */ len = ufget(bindname, buf, CHUNKSIZE); totlen = abs(len); /* Set total length */ while ( len < 0 ) /* More to come */ { /* Make room for next chunk */ buf = realloc(buf, totlen+CHUNKSIZE); /* Get next chunk */ len = ufgetc(bindname, buf+totlen, CHUNKSIZE); /* Update total length */ totlen += abs(len); } buf = realloc(buf, totlen+1); /* Make room for terminator */ buf[totlen] = 0; /* Add terminator */ } Copy Related Links ufget Get data from a field displayed in a Uniface component. ugetbind Get the internal bind name of a Uniface field. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}